#. Tag: para
#: ch05.xml:84
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"So money can't purchase influence, but it can purchase things that "
"<emphasis>lead to</emphasis> influence. The most obvious example is "
"programmers. If good programmers are hired, and they stick around long "
"enough to get experience with the software and credibility in the community, "
"then they can influence the project by the same means as any other member. "
"They will have a vote, or if there are many of them, they will have a voting "
