#. Tag: para
#: ch05.xml:114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Separate organizations with related software needs often find themselves "
"duplicating effort, either by redundantly writing similar code in-house, or "
"by purchasing similar products from proprietary vendors. When they realize "
"what's going on, the organizations may pool their resources and create (or "
"join) an open source project tailored to their needs. The advantages are "
"obvious: the costs of development are divided, but the benefits accrue to "
