"knows all the old arguments that have been hashed and rehashed on the "
"discussion lists. A new developer, having no memory of those conversations, "
"may try to raise the topics again, leading to a loss of credibility for your "
"organization; the others might wonder \"Can't they remember anything?\" A "
"new developer will also have no political feel for the project's "
"personalities, and will not be able to influence development directions as "
"quickly or as smoothly as one who's been around a long time."
