"discusi√≥n como che gustar√≠a. Este √© un dos compromisos que adoptas para "
"ter unha comunidade de desenvolvemento f√≥ra da t√∫a n√≥mina."

#. Tag: title
#: ch05.xml:470
#, no-c-format
msgid "Money Can't Buy You Love"
msgstr "Os Cartos Non Poden Comprar o Amor"

#. Tag: para
#: ch05.xml:472
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you're a paid developer on a project, then set guidelines early on about "
"what the money can and cannot buy. This does not mean you need to post twice "
"a day to the mailing lists reiterating your noble and incorruptible nature. "
"It merely means that you should be on the lookout for opportunities to "
"defuse the tensions that <emphasis>could</emphasis> be created by money. You "
"don't need to start out assuming that the tensions are there; you do need to "
"demonstrate an awareness that they have the potential to arise."
msgstr ""
"Se es un desenvolvedor asalariado nun proxecto, ent√≥n establece axi√±a as  "
"normas sobre o que os cartos poden comprar e o que non. Isto non significa "
"que te√±as que mandar d√∫as mensaxes ao d√≠a √°s roldas de correo reiterando "
"a t√∫a nobre e incorruptible natureza. Simplemente significa que debes estar "
"atento para desfacer as tensi√≥ns que <emphasis>poder√≠an</emphasis> ser "
"creadas polos cartos. Non debes comezar asumindo que as tensi√≥ns est√°n "
"a√≠; o preciso √© demostrar que est√°s ao tanto de que potencialmente poden "
"xurdir."

#. Tag: para
#: ch05.xml:481
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A perfect example of this came up in the Subversion project. Subversion was "
"started in 2000 by <ulink url=\"http://www.collab.net/\">CollabNet</ulink>, "
"which has been the project's primary funder since its inception, paying the "
"salaries of several developers (disclaimer: I'm one of them). Soon after the "
"project began, we hired another developer, Mike Pilato, to join the effort. "
"By then, coding had already started. Although Subversion was still very much "
"in the early stages, it already had a development community with a set of "
"basic ground rules."
msgstr ""
"Un exemplo perfecto disto xurdiu no proxecto Subversion. Subversion arrancou "
"en 2000 grazas a <ulink url=\\\"http://www.collab.net/\\\">CollabNet</"
"ulink>, o cal √© o principal financieiro do proxecto dende a s√∫a "
"concepci√≥n, pagando os salarios de varios desenvolvedores (nota: eu son un "
"deles). Pouco despois do comezo do proxecto, contratamos outro "
"desenvolvedor, Mike Pilato, para unirse ao esforzo. Daquela, a escritura de "
"c√≥digo xa tivera comezado.\n"
"A pesares de que Subversion a√≠nda estaba nas s√∫as etapas iniciais, xa hab√≠"
"a unha comunidade de desenvolvemento con un conxunto de normas b√°sicas."

#. Tag: para
#: ch05.xml:491
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Mike's arrival raised an interesting question. Subversion already had a "
"policy about how a new developer gets commit access. First, he submits some "
"patches to the development mailing list. After enough patches have gone by "
"for the other committers to see that the new contributor knows what he's "
"doing, someone proposes that he just commit directly (that proposal is "
"private, as described in <xref linkend=\"committers\"/>). Assuming the "
"committers agree, one of them mails the new developer and offers him direct "
"commit access to the project's repository."
msgstr ""
"A chegada de Mike fixo xurdir unha cuesti√≥n interesante. Subversion xa "
"ti√±a unha pol√≠tica sobre como os novos desenvolvedores consegu√≠an acceso "
"para facer commit (gravaci√≥n de cambios no repositorio central do c√≥digo "
"fonte). Primeiro, deb√≠an enviar alg√∫ns parches √°s roldas de correo de "
"desenvolvemento. Despois dun n√∫mero suficiente de parches para que o resto "
"de desenvolvedores puidesen ver que o novo contribu√≠nte sab√≠a o que estaba "
"a facer, algu√©n propo√±√≠a que simplemente fixera commit directamente (esta "
"proposta era privada, como se describe en <xref linkend=\"committers\"/>). "
"Asumindo o acordo dos desenvolvedores con acceso a facer commit, un deles "
"envi√°balle un correo √≥ novo desenvolvedor e ofrec√≠alle acceso a facer "
"commit no repositorio do proxecto."

#. Tag: para
#: ch05.xml:501
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"CollabNet had hired Mike specifically to work on Subversion. Among those who "
