"a very good relationship with the CollabNet employees, and most likely would "
"not have objected if we'd just given Mike commit access the day he was "
"hired. But we knew we'd be setting a precedent. If we granted Mike commit "
"access by fiat, we'd be saying that CollabNet had the right to ignore "
"project guidelines, simply because it was the primary funder. While the "
"damage from this would not necessarily be immediately apparent, it would "
"gradually result in the non-salaried developers feeling disenfranchised. "
"Other people have to earn their commit access&mdash;CollabNet just buys it."
msgstr ""
"CollabNet ti√±a contratado a Mike especificamente para traballar en "
"Subversion. Entre os que xa o co√±ec√≠an, non hab√≠a d√∫bida sobre as s√∫as "
"capacidades t√©cnicas ou a s√∫a preparaci√≥n para traballar no proxecto. "
"Ademais, os desenvolvedores voluntarios ti√±an unha moi boa relaci√≥n cos "
"empregados de CollabNet, e presumiblemente a maior√≠a non plantexar√≠a "
"obxecci√≥ns se lle d√©ramos a Mike acceso a facer commit o d√≠a que o "
